column4: there might be something under ~/.config/autostart or /etc/xdg/autostart that you could manually try to remove
do you know what gdl_box.autostart is?
no i don't .. but looking inside that file might show some light on things
have you opened that autostart file with an editor ? should be regular .desktop syntax in there, with a program name and exec line inside
i checked both folders there is just Cairo-dock and that is right, but this session-dialog of cairo-dock is the problem, but i definately guess that gnome autosave session occured this problem
that gdl_box was google desktop i also removed that
i will try if that fixed that cairo-sttings-dialog-problem too
oh well it did, **** google desktop, ill teach my console four words sudo aptitude remove google-desktop
very well all my current issues are gone, now i can focus on bugging MSI-ticket-system with request on producing 64bit drivers for a new tv-stick :D
seems like that will not work, but its kinda fun to because i work at a call entry for it-support for a huge corporation
can't win 'em all i guess, having an issue-free ubuntu makes good though
dont the users have to ask the manufactures for more linux support?
sure, no argument there, all for that .. it has greatly improved ( a few exceptions aside)
what msi needs to do is take there pc on that they precompiled the driver for kernel 2.6.22 and above
make it 64bit hardware install that 64bit kernel and recompile that driver with --force-architecture
